At NeoMate, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of your information when you use our app and website.
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully before using our app or website. By accessing or using our app or website, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with these terms, please do not use our app or website.
Information Collection
While using NeoMate, we may collect the following types of information:
a. Anonymous Tracking Information: We collect anonymous tracking information to help us understand how our app and website are being used, and to improve the quality of our services. This information may include, but is not limited to, device information, app usage data, and IP addresses.
b. Google Analytics: We use Google Analytics to monitor app performance and gather information about app usage. Google Analytics may collect information such as your device’s IP address, browser type, operating system, and other similar data. This information is anonymized and cannot be used to personally identify you. You can learn more about Google’s privacy practices by visiting their Privacy Policy.
Use of Collected Information
We use the collected information to:
a. Monitor and analyse usage and trends to improve our app and website.
b. Provide, maintain, and improve our app and website.
c. Ensure the security and stability of our app and website.
Information Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personally identifiable information to third parties. We may share aggregated, anonymized information with trusted third parties, such as Google Analytics, to help us understand app usage and improve our services. These third parties are contractually obligated to keep your information confidential and use it only for the purposes for which we disclose it to them.
Security
We are committed to protecting the security of your information. We use industry-standard security measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes to this Privacy Policy will be posted on this page, and we will update the “last updated” date at the top of this policy. Your continued use of our app and website after any changes to this Privacy Policy indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.
